Definition: A location or structure in the body, including tissues, regions, cavities, and spaces; for example, right elbow, or left ventricle of the heart.
unique id for the element within a resource (for internal references). This may be any string value that does not contain spaces.
Code for the anatomical location or landmark, without laterality, direction, or other modifiers needed to completely specify the body site.
Anatomical location or specimen further detailing the side(s) of interest.
How far the anatomical location of interest is from the given landmark
Anatomical location or specimen further detailing directionality.
A direction indicated by an angle relative to 12 o'clock.
A text note containing additional details, explanation, description, comment, or summarization.
A file that contains audio, video, image, or similar content.

Short: identifies the meaning of the extension
Definition: Source of the definition for the extension code - a logical name or a URL.
Value of extension - may be a resource or one of a constrained set of the data types (see Extensibility in the spec for list).
